MultiUser Access to Hive
If you are only making a JDBC connection as a privileged user from a single blessed machine, then direct proxy access is the simpler approach. You can just pass the user you need to impersonate in the JDBC URL by using the hive.server2.proxy.user=<user> parameter.

DelegationUID option doesn't work with JDBC driver with or without Knox. hive.server2.proxy.user option does work without knox. hive.server2.proxy.user has no impact when connection is made through knox.



Property to Print summary of iO
set hive.tez.exec.print.summary=true

set hive.log.explain.output=true
set hive.explain.user=true
set hive.query.results.cache.enabled=false;

#Parameters decides if query will run on hiveserver2 or on daemons.

hive.fetch.task.conversion.threshold
hive.fetch.task.conversion
hive.fetch.task.aggr



# Hive LLAP status
hive --service llapstatus --name llap0
